hopobject.body: Your cash is being counted http //awccanadianpharmacy.com review Researchers believe that drinking too much soda can lower the bodyâs potassium levels. High fructose corn syrup and caffeine, both key ingredients in many sodas, are diuretics. So when you consume too much of them, they can lead to excessive urine production and diarrhea that flush potassium from the body, says study author Dr. Nadir Saoudi, chief of cardiology at the Princesse Grace Medical Centre in Monaco. Caffeine may also keep the kidneys, which regulate potassium levels, from properly doing their job.
